Installing Postgresql from Source:-

sudo apt-get install zlib1g-dev libreadline6-dev gcc make
sudo apt-get install bison
sudo apt-get install flex

Then exactly follow the instructions given in

http://www.thegeekstuff.com/2009/04/linux-postgresql-install-and-configure-from-source/

After making changes to source code configure, make and make install then restart server using the following command:-

/usr/local/pgsql/bin/pg_ctl restart -D /usr/local/pgsql/data/
